I get it.

252
00:22:33,101 --> 00:22:34,602
I don't think you do.

253
00:22:34,686 --> 00:22:36,604
But you're about to.

254
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:39,232
And so will that idiot sheriff
and his wife.

255
00:22:41,818 --> 00:22:43,361
And your little dog too!

256
00:23:02,547 --> 00:23:03,714
Pitiful.

257
00:23:03,798 --> 00:23:06,425
What? Who are you?

258
00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:10,597
Where are my manners?

259
00:23:11,306 --> 00:23:14,684
Sonic, meet Knuckles.

260
00:23:14,767 --> 00:23:16,977
My new BFFAE.

261
00:23:17,061 --> 00:23:20,439
Bestest friend forever and ever!

262
00:23:20,523 --> 00:23:23,651
Look, Robotnik, I don't care
who you brought to help you.

263
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:25,570
You're never going to get my power.

264
00:23:25,653 --> 00:23:28,238
Do I look like I need your power?

265
00:23:38,791 --> 00:23:43,003
So nice when diabolical evil
lives up to the hype.

266
00:23:46,007 --> 00:23:47,341
Where is it?

267
00:23:47,425 --> 00:23:50,469
You want it? Here it comes.

268
00:23:50,553 --> 00:23:55,053
I was expecting more of you.
You're unskilled.

269
00:23:56,059 --> 00:23:57,310
Untrained.

270
00:23:58,853 --> 00:24:01,188
And unworthy!

271
00:24:02,649 --> 00:24:06,194
You forgot one. Unstoppable.

272
00:24:32,136 --> 00:24:35,973
It is my destiny
to do what my ancestors could not--

273
00:24:36,057 --> 00:24:40,227
To restore the ultimate power
to the home of my people.

274
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:44,773
Ultimate power?
I don't know what you're talking about.

275
00:24:44,857 --> 00:24:46,066
You've got the wrong guy.

276
00:24:46,150 --> 00:24:48,318
Ultimate power?

277
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:51,614
Now you're speaking my language.

278
00:24:51,698 --> 00:24:54,867
Don't play dumb with me,
apprentice of Longclaw.

279
00:24:54,951 --> 00:24:56,410
You knew Longclaw?

280
00:24:56,494 --> 00:25:00,623
Longclaw and her people were
the sworn enemy of my tribe, the Echidna.

281
00:25:00,707 --> 00:25:05,207
We fought and died at their hands,
and now you will die at mine.

282
00:25:16,389 --> 00:25:18,557
Come on. Get in! I'm on your side.

283
00:25:18,641 --> 00:25:20,559
I'm sorry. Who are you?

284
00:25:21,811 --> 00:25:23,521
You know what? It doesn't matter.

285
00:25:26,065 --> 00:25:28,108
Get us out of here! Go, go, go!

286
00:25:32,321 --> 00:25:33,322
He's gone rabid!

287
00:25:35,575 --> 00:25:36,993
Gross! Is he licking it?

288
00:25:38,202 --> 00:25:39,494
See ya!

289
00:25:39,579 --> 00:25:41,872
Make sure to get your shots, Eggman!

290
00:25:55,762 --> 00:25:59,432
Wow. Okay. Let me just say
it is an honor to finally meet you, Sonic.

291
00:25:59,515 --> 00:26:01,058
Is it okay if I call you Sonic?

292
00:26:01,142 --> 00:26:03,894
Everyone calls me Tails.
You're probably wondering why.

293
00:26:03,978 --> 00:26:06,355
Let me guess. Because of the extra tail?

294
00:26:06,439 --> 00:26:08,357
That's right!
I should've known you'd get that.

295
00:26:08,441 --> 00:26:12,153
Cool. Also, what is going on?
Robotnik's back?

296
00:26:12,236 --> 00:26:14,696
And who is
Clifford the Big Red Rage Monster?

297
00:26:15,364 --> 00:26:17,324
That's Knuckles, the last of the Echidnas

298
00:26:17,408 --> 00:26:19,827
and the most dangerous warrior
in the galaxy.

299
00:26:19,911 --> 00:26:21,996
He's obsessed with finding
the Master Emerald.

300
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:24,415
Are you serious? The Master Emerald?

301
00:26:24,499 --> 00:26:26,125
That's just a bedtime story.

302
00:26:26,209 --> 00:26:27,627
Well, he believes it's real.

303
00:26:27,710 --> 00:26:30,003
And he must think
you're the key to finding it.

304
00:26:32,215 --> 00:26:34,050
Red light! Give me the wheel!

305
00:26:34,133 --> 00:26:35,968
-Hey, what are you--
-Move your foot.

306
00:26:43,726 --> 00:26:45,018
I think we lost him.

307
00:26:52,944 --> 00:26:55,529
We did not lose him.
We definitely did not lose him!

308
00:27:00,785 --> 00:27:02,953
I've got an idea. Do you trust me?

309
00:27:03,037 --> 00:27:05,247
Of course not! I literally just met you!

310
00:27:05,331 --> 00:27:07,416
-Just let me-- Come on!
-What are you doing?

311
00:27:26,394 --> 00:27:27,645
We're flying.

312
00:27:28,354 --> 00:27:30,439
Did your butt just turn into a helicopter?

313
00:27:31,816 --> 00:27:33,442
A butt-copter!

314
00:27:34,026 --> 00:27:37,362
Only Sonic the Hedgehog
could come up with something like that.

315
00:27:52,461 --> 00:27:54,629
Foxy move.

316
00:27:55,882 --> 00:27:57,925
You want something done right...

317
00:27:59,218 --> 00:28:02,221
you have to hire someone
you can push around.

318
00:28:04,390 --> 00:28:05,265
All caps.

319
00:28:23,618 --> 00:28:24,910
Doctor,

320
00:28:25,828 --> 00:28:26,954
where are you?

321
00:28:33,753 --> 00:28:34,795
Freak.

322
00:28:43,054 --> 00:28:45,347
I'm sorry, folks.

323
00:28:45,431 --> 00:28:47,808
I have to close early. Everybody out!

324
00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:50,978
Everybody out.
Thank you for visiting the Mean Bean.

325
00:28:51,062 --> 00:28:53,105
All right, good night. Good night.

326
00:29:12,291 --> 00:29:13,333
He's back.

327
00:29:15,044 --> 00:29:17,046
He's back!

328
00:30:11,809 --> 00:30:14,019
That's more like it.

329
00:30:15,021 --> 00:30:17,857
I've been re-hatched!

330
00:30:29,410 --> 00:30:33,910
So, my massively metacarpaled friend,

331
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:35,374
you mentioned...

332
00:30:37,251 --> 00:30:39,253
ultimate power.

333
00:30:39,337 --> 00:30:40,338
Back at the house?

334
00:30:40,421 --> 00:30:42,047
The Master Emerald?

335
00:30:42,131 --> 00:30:43,507
It does not concern you.

336
00:30:43,591 --> 00:30:46,594
I got you off that planet
and you brought me to the hedgehog.

337
00:30:46,677 --> 00:30:48,762
We have no more use for each other.

338
00:30:48,846 --> 00:30:51,181
Well, I hate to be a contrarian, but...

339
00:30:52,099 --> 00:30:53,225
I think we might.

340
00:30:54,727 --> 00:30:57,187
You think these machines
are a match for me?

341
00:30:57,271 --> 00:31:00,732
I will shatter them
like the bones from a fallen--

342
00:31:01,609 --> 00:31:02,735
They are stairs.

343
00:31:08,449 --> 00:31:12,619
You see, Earth is my turf, G.

344
00:31:13,120 --> 00:31:15,872
If you don't know how to floss,
you'll be lost without me.

345
00:31:15,956 --> 00:31:18,500
I understand nothing
of what you just said.

346
00:31:18,584 --> 00:31:22,963
I help you retrieve the Emerald,
and you use it to...

347
00:31:24,256 --> 00:31:28,756
destroy the hedgehog!

348
00:31:29,970 --> 00:31:31,680
You're suggesting an alliance.

349
00:31:31,764 --> 00:31:35,893
Around here we simply
grip each other's hands tightly.

350
00:31:41,273 --> 00:31:44,901
You truculent space bumpkin!

351
00:31:44,985 --> 00:31:47,153
You've crushed my favorite hand!

352
00:31:47,822 --> 00:31:49,740
Really? My hand is uninjured.

353
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:53,202
But I'm now convinced of your commitment.

354
00:31:53,285 --> 00:31:55,203
"Oh, goody,"

355
00:31:55,287 --> 00:31:58,790
he exclaimed,
while he reset two of his knuckles.

356
00:31:58,874 --> 00:32:01,209
I'm...

357
00:32:01,293 --> 00:32:05,793
delighted to be on the same team.

358
00:32:14,140 --> 00:32:15,432
Road trip!

359
00:32:16,016 --> 00:32:18,059
I'll let you stick your nose
out the window.

360
00:32:20,271 --> 00:32:22,022
Sonic, where are we?

361
00:32:22,106 --> 00:32:24,483
Welcome to the Wade Cave.

362
00:32:24,567 --> 00:32:27,611
Which is something
I hope to someday say to a woman.

363
00:32:27,695 --> 00:32:29,363
A woman who's not my mom.

364
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:31,407
Wade, focus.

365
00:32:31,490 --> 00:32:35,202
We need to figure out why Knuckles thinks
I'm the key to finding the Master Emerald.

366
00:32:35,286 --> 00:32:37,204
And why did he mention Longclaw?

367
00:32:37,788 --> 00:32:40,040
There must be a connection.

368
00:32:40,624 --> 00:32:42,042
Wait a minute. There is.

369
00:32:42,585 --> 00:32:46,505
Look. There's an emerald symbol
on the map Longclaw gave me.

370
00:32:46,589 --> 00:32:48,465
I never knew what it meant before.

371
00:32:49,175 --> 00:32:50,843
Something's happening.

372
00:33:03,981 --> 00:33:05,357
Longclaw?

373
00:33:05,441 --> 00:33:06,984
Hello, Sonic.

374
00:33:07,067 --> 00:33:10,445
If you're watching this,
then something has happened to me.

375
00:33:10,529 --> 00:33:13,365
And I pray
you've made it to Earth unharmed.

376
00:33:13,866 --> 00:33:18,161
This world has been chosen
for a very important reason.

377
00:33:18,245 --> 00:33:21,873
It's the secret location
of the Master Emerald.

378
00:33:24,001 --> 00:33:27,629
The Emerald has the power
to turn thoughts into reality.

379
00:33:28,130 --> 00:33:30,632
Like the Stay Puft Marshmallow Man
from Ghostbusters.

380
00:33:31,383 --> 00:33:35,470
In the wrong hands it could threaten
all life in the universe.

381
00:33:35,554 --> 00:33:38,473
Protecting the Emerald was my sacred duty.

382
00:33:38,557 --> 00:33:42,227
And now I must pass
that responsibility to you.

383
00:33:43,354 --> 00:33:46,023
This is my moment.

384
00:33:46,106 --> 00:33:49,567
Follow the map, find the Emerald,
and keep it safe.

385
00:33:50,194 --> 00:33:51,737
My dear Sonic,

386
00:33:51,820 --> 00:33:54,781
you have a heart
like no creature I've ever known.

387
00:33:55,407 --> 00:33:57,075
I love you so much.

388
00:33:58,744 --> 00:33:59,953
Goodbye.

389
00:34:01,330 --> 00:34:03,123
No, no, wait.

390
00:34:10,256 --> 00:34:12,132
I won't let you down, Longclaw.

391
00:34:14,093 --> 00:34:17,221
So is that your dad?

392
00:34:17,304 --> 00:34:18,763
What?

393
00:34:18,847 --> 00:34:19,722
No?

394
00:34:20,599 --> 00:34:23,435
According to this map,
the first clue is in Siberia.

395
00:34:23,519 --> 00:34:25,812
It's a compass
that will lead to the Emerald.

396
00:34:25,896 --> 00:34:28,815
And with Knuckles already here,
it's a race.

397
00:34:28,899 --> 00:34:29,900
Knuckles?

398
00:34:30,651 --> 00:34:32,444
I knew a kid in middle school
named Knuckles.

399
00:34:32,528 --> 00:34:34,363
Could fit his whole fist in his mouth.

400
00:34:34,446 --> 00:34:38,575
If this is the same Knuckles,
we are screwed.

401
00:34:38,659 --> 00:34:41,078
This Knuckles, that Knuckles.
It doesn't matter.

402
00:34:41,161 --> 00:34:42,829
We're gonna get there first.

403
00:34:45,833 --> 00:34:47,584
What do you mean, "we"?

404
00:34:47,668 --> 00:34:48,960
You're coming with me.

405
00:34:49,044 --> 00:34:50,378
No, no, no.

406
00:34:50,462 --> 00:34:53,673
I just came here to warn you.
I'm not a field guy.

407
00:34:53,757 --> 00:34:57,552
Don't worry. I got your back.
I won't let anything happen to you.

408
00:34:59,013 --> 00:35:02,766
It's a power bump.
On Earth, it means an unbreakable promise.

409
00:35:02,850 --> 00:35:05,561
Okay, I'm in.

410
00:35:21,285 --> 00:35:23,662
Doctor. It's really you.

411
00:35:24,580 --> 00:35:26,123
You look different.

412
00:35:26,749 --> 00:35:29,418
Papa's got a brand new 'stache.

413
00:35:32,546 --> 00:35:36,174
I knew it. I knew it!
I knew you'd come back, sir.

414
00:35:36,258 --> 00:35:38,677
I never stopped steaming
your Austrian goat's milk.

415
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:45,934
Could use some mushroom.

416
00:35:47,811 --> 00:35:48,978
You brought something.

417
00:35:49,730 --> 00:35:52,524
Some kind of space porcupine.

418
00:35:53,025 --> 00:35:56,028
Porcupine? I am an Echidna!

419
00:35:56,111 --> 00:35:58,696
Trained since birth
in all forms of lethal combat,

420
00:35:58,781 --> 00:36:00,991
destined to restore honor to my tribe,

421
00:36:01,075 --> 00:36:04,870
and willing to destroy
anything that gets in my way.

422
00:36:05,496 --> 00:36:06,872
Welcome to the team.

423
00:36:13,087 --> 00:36:15,005
That means he trusts you, Stone.

424
00:36:15,631 --> 00:36:18,342
Now let's renovate this dump!

425
00:36:19,009 --> 00:36:21,344
Latte with steamed Austrian goat milk!

426
00:36:41,657 --> 00:36:42,908
Good one. Solid.

427
00:36:50,124 --> 00:36:51,458
-Sorry, fellas.
-That's game!

428
00:36:52,584 --> 00:36:54,210
That's how we do!

429
00:36:54,795 --> 00:36:57,172
-But are they good at math?
-Teamwork makes the dream work!

430
00:36:57,798 --> 00:36:59,132
Sorry about that, Big Tom.

431
00:36:59,758 --> 00:37:01,801
-Are you good?
-All good. Fine.

432
00:37:01,885 --> 00:37:04,929
Thanks for inviting me out to hang
with you and your groomsmen.

433
00:37:05,013 --> 00:37:06,514
Good quality bonding.

434
00:37:07,141 --> 00:37:08,308
You know, bro,

435
00:37:08,392 --> 00:37:10,894
those guys right there,
they're way more than my groomsmen.

436
00:37:10,978 --> 00:37:12,104
That's my squad.

437
00:37:12,187 --> 00:37:14,230
Never would've made it through life
without 'em.

438
00:37:14,314 --> 00:37:15,356
Get over here!

439
00:37:15,441 --> 00:37:17,151
Yeah, I'm coming!

440
00:37:17,735 --> 00:37:20,446
-I'll catch you later.
-Hey. Yeah!

441
00:37:20,529 --> 00:37:22,822
Let me know if you're ready
for some power yoga.

442
00:37:22,906 --> 00:37:25,950
-You bet.
-Come on, Tommy boy. Let's go.

443
00:37:26,034 --> 00:37:27,076
Don't make me.

444
00:37:28,162 --> 00:37:29,246
What am I doing?

445
00:37:29,329 --> 00:37:30,621
Hey, Uncle Tommy!

446
00:37:30,706 --> 00:37:32,207
Hey, girls!

447
00:37:32,291 --> 00:37:35,127
-How you do-- Are those the wedding rings?
-Uh-huh.

448
00:37:35,711 --> 00:37:36,712
May 1?

449
00:37:36,795 --> 00:37:40,256
This little ring bearer
has been taking her job very seriously.

450
00:37:40,340 --> 00:37:42,675
-She's been practicing all morning.
-I can see that.

451
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:45,137
How very responsible of you.

452
00:37:45,220 --> 00:37:46,888
Except aren't there supposed
to be two wedding rings?

453
00:37:47,514 --> 00:37:48,640
Uh-oh.

454
00:37:49,892 --> 00:37:53,312
-Uncle Tommy?
-Hang on. What's going on here?

455
00:37:55,731 --> 00:37:56,940
You're gonna do great, kiddo.

456
00:37:57,024 --> 00:37:58,066
Bye.

457
00:37:58,150 --> 00:37:59,526
-Hey, baby

458
00:38:02,654 --> 00:38:04,656
That's right! Groom in the building!

459
00:38:04,740 --> 00:38:06,199
Look at those guys.

460
00:38:06,784 --> 00:38:08,202
I wish Sonic had that.

461
00:38:08,744 --> 00:38:10,954
-Muscles?
-Control yourself.

462
00:38:12,039 --> 00:38:15,667
No. Buddies. Wingmen. A squad.

463
00:38:15,751 --> 00:38:19,254
Sonic doesn't have anything like that.
He's flying solo.

464
00:38:20,130 --> 00:38:22,090
Baby, you got to relax.

465
00:38:22,174 --> 00:38:24,384
You're at the Four Seasons.

466
00:38:24,468 --> 00:38:27,387
Have a mai tai.
Spend some time with your wife.

467
00:38:27,471 --> 00:38:30,557
That's what he said.
Seriously, his exact words.

468
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:34,686
See? He's a smart kid. He'll find his way.

469
00:38:35,270 --> 00:38:38,356
I absolutely cannot find my way.

470
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:41,776
We are completely, totally,
unequivocally lost.

471
00:38:43,237 --> 00:38:44,696
Sonic, in this weather,

472
00:38:44,780 --> 00:38:47,783
there's no way we're gonna get
any readings on this thing!

473
00:38:47,866 --> 00:38:49,617
-Should we go back?
-No, no, no.

474
00:38:49,701 --> 00:38:52,954
There's a light up ahead.
Maybe we can take shelter in there.

475
00:38:58,544 --> 00:38:59,628
Perfect.

476
00:38:59,711 --> 00:39:02,880
Are you sure about this?
We don't know who's inside.

477
00:39:02,965 --> 00:39:06,218
Don't worry.
On Earth, people are very welcoming,

478
00:39:06,301 --> 00:39:09,679
and love taking complete strangers
into their homes.

479
00:39:39,835 --> 00:39:40,794
Run.

480
00:39:43,422 --> 00:39:45,006
Table for two, please!

481
00:39:47,134 --> 00:39:49,344
What would you like to order?

482
00:39:49,428 --> 00:39:51,138
Two beef stews, please.

483
00:39:56,602 --> 00:39:59,771
-Where'd you get all these cool gadgets?
-I invented 'em.

484
00:39:59,855 --> 00:40:01,773
That's kinda my thing.

485
00:40:01,857 --> 00:40:04,317
In fact,
my inventions are how I discovered you.

486
00:40:05,152 --> 00:40:07,487
Remember that night at the baseball field?

487
00:40:07,571 --> 00:40:11,283
Your energy blast reached all the way
to my home planet.

488
00:40:11,366 --> 00:40:15,866
I saw you save your whole village
from that crazy mustache guy.

489
00:40:16,079 --> 00:40:19,290
Wait, so you've been watching me
this whole time?

490
00:40:19,374 --> 00:40:20,958
Even in the shower?

491
00:40:21,043 --> 00:40:22,961
That's a trick question.

492
00:40:23,045 --> 00:40:25,255
Sonic the Hedgehog prefers bubble baths.

493
00:40:25,339 --> 00:40:26,673
Man, you're good!

494
00:40:26,757 --> 00:40:29,217
When I learned Knuckles was on your trail,

495
00:40:29,301 --> 00:40:32,137
I knew I couldn't just sit back
and watch anymore.

496
00:40:32,220 --> 00:40:33,679
I had to come warn you.

497
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:36,600
What? Hang on one sec.

498
00:40:36,683 --> 00:40:38,267
Donut Lord is checking in.

499
00:40:40,354 --> 00:40:43,899
"Just chilling. Watching TV."

500
00:40:44,399 --> 00:40:46,150
Dot, dot, dot.

501
00:40:46,860 --> 00:40:48,987
Dot, dot, dot.

502
00:40:49,738 --> 00:40:51,448
Dot, dot, dot.

503
00:40:51,531 --> 00:40:53,324
Dot, dot, dot.

504
00:40:53,909 --> 00:40:56,494
Dot, dot, dot.

505
00:40:56,995 --> 00:40:57,996
Doctor,

506
00:40:58,997 --> 00:41:01,332
why are we working with this imbecile?

507
00:41:02,668 --> 00:41:07,168
Because that simpleminded space trash
is the key to something extraordinary.

508
00:41:08,173 --> 00:41:10,717
Something to help you get revenge
on the hedgehog.

509
