or the world is doomed.

764
01:01:56,045 --> 01:01:57,171
Tails!

765
01:01:57,254 --> 01:02:00,715
-Wait! All this happened since yesterday?
-Wait. Who's Tails?

766
01:02:00,799 --> 01:02:02,050
Tails, can you hear me?

767
01:02:02,134 --> 01:02:04,094
Oh, Lord, there are two of them now.

768
01:02:04,178 --> 01:02:06,346
Okay, let me think. Tails, come on, buddy.

769
01:02:11,101 --> 01:02:12,477
Hey!

770
01:02:12,561 --> 01:02:14,729
Randall, why do all of your friends
have weapons?

771
01:02:16,815 --> 01:02:20,068
You really should have taken me up
on that brunch, Mr. and Mrs. Wachowski.

772
01:02:20,861 --> 01:02:21,903
Olive Garden guy?

773
01:02:21,987 --> 01:02:24,531
It's okay, everyone. We're federal agents.

774
01:02:25,908 --> 01:02:27,784
You, too, Agent. Go ahead.

775
01:02:34,291 --> 01:02:38,378
You mean to tell me
that this entire wedding was a setup?

776
01:02:38,462 --> 01:02:40,172
-Rachel, wait a minute.
-What?

777
01:02:40,256 --> 01:02:41,340
That's correct, ma'am.

778
01:02:41,423 --> 01:02:44,801
Every single aspect of Operation Catfish
was a complete fabrication.

779
01:02:45,970 --> 01:02:47,388
Operation Catfish?

780
01:02:48,180 --> 01:02:49,764
So is everyone here an agent?

781
01:02:51,225 --> 01:02:52,392
Are you an agent?

782
01:02:53,227 --> 01:02:54,394
Son of a...

783
01:02:54,895 --> 01:02:58,231
Was the florist an agent?
How about the photographer?

784
01:02:58,857 --> 01:03:00,358
The woman who waxed my...

785
01:03:01,360 --> 01:03:02,444
at the spa?

786
01:03:04,446 --> 01:03:06,448
-Is Jojo an agent?
-Rachel.

787
01:03:07,116 --> 01:03:09,118
-What?
-Rachel, listen to me.

788
01:03:09,201 --> 01:03:12,287
I'm done listening! I am done listening!

789
01:03:12,830 --> 01:03:15,833
I am so sorry. I am so sorry.

790
01:03:15,916 --> 01:03:17,500
I really am. I am so sorry.

791
01:03:19,461 --> 01:03:21,129
No. Hey, no!

792
01:03:22,506 --> 01:03:24,674
Let him go! Hey!

793
01:03:27,636 --> 01:03:28,803
Sonic, hang on.

794
01:03:29,847 --> 01:03:31,974
-Take it easy. It's not worth it.
-Tom!

795
01:03:32,891 --> 01:03:35,476
Sonic is not a threat. He's on our side.

796
01:03:35,561 --> 01:03:37,479
He's an uncontrolled extraterrestrial.

797
01:03:37,563 --> 01:03:39,648
And your days of aiding
and abetting him are over.

798
01:03:40,399 --> 01:03:42,442
Secure them in the hotel
until the chopper arrives.

799
01:03:43,193 --> 01:03:44,444
You're making a mistake.

800
01:03:44,528 --> 01:03:46,071
Hold on, Major A-hole!

801
01:03:46,739 --> 01:03:48,323
This is still my day,

802
01:03:48,407 --> 01:03:52,119
and someone is gonna explain to me
what the hell is going on here!

803
01:03:52,202 --> 01:03:55,538
After the events in San Francisco,
a global task force was created,

804
01:03:55,622 --> 01:03:58,833
devoted to protecting our planet
from alien threats.

805
01:03:58,917 --> 01:04:01,586
That day,
Guardian Units of Nations was born.

806
01:04:01,670 --> 01:04:04,255
-G-U-N. Seriously?
-GUN, yeah.

807
01:04:04,340 --> 01:04:06,925
Look, what about protecting our planet
from Dr. Robotnik?

808
01:04:08,260 --> 01:04:09,636
Robotnik is dead.

809
01:04:09,720 --> 01:04:11,805
You're wrong. He's back.

810
01:04:11,889 --> 01:04:14,308
And you just hauled away the only ones
who could stop him.

811
01:04:17,353 --> 01:04:19,063
Sounds like Robotnik
might be back in play.

812
01:04:19,146 --> 01:04:21,648
If he is, I want him found immediately.

813
01:04:22,983 --> 01:04:25,151
And cancel my five o'clock
at the Olive Garden.

814
01:04:25,652 --> 01:04:27,278
-Aunt Maddie?
-Yeah.

815
01:04:27,363 --> 01:04:29,031
Sonic and his friend dropped this.

816
01:04:35,871 --> 01:04:37,289
I have an idea.

817
01:04:37,373 --> 01:04:39,541
And I want to have a word with my fiancé.

818
01:04:39,625 --> 01:04:41,251
And that word is "murder."

819
01:04:46,715 --> 01:04:48,758
Hey, come on.
You can't just leave us in here.

820
01:04:48,842 --> 01:04:51,970
My friend is hurt!
He needs a doctor, a vet, anyone!

821
01:04:53,389 --> 01:04:56,183
Tails, you got to wake up, buddy.
Please wake up.

822
01:05:04,525 --> 01:05:05,651
All clear.

823
01:05:09,279 --> 01:05:10,863
All right. Game plan.

824
01:05:10,948 --> 01:05:13,909
I get inside the hotel and find
where they're hiding Tom and Sonic.

825
01:05:13,992 --> 01:05:15,618
Then I find Randall, right?

826
01:05:15,702 --> 01:05:17,120
And then I squeeze the breath

827
01:05:17,204 --> 01:05:21,291
from his lying, deceitful,
perfectly manscaped body!

828
01:05:23,669 --> 01:05:25,379
I'm going through a lot right now.

829
01:05:25,462 --> 01:05:28,548
-So let me process this my own way, okay?
-Sure, sure.

830
01:05:29,216 --> 01:05:30,842
-No judgment.
-Should've brought a journal.

831
01:05:30,926 --> 01:05:32,302
Okay--

832
01:05:32,386 --> 01:05:35,931
Okay. Is this meant to be a weapon?
This is adorable.

833
01:05:37,099 --> 01:05:38,141
Take that, Randall!

834
01:05:39,059 --> 01:05:40,268
Run, Randall!

835
01:05:40,352 --> 01:05:41,770
All right.

836
01:05:41,854 --> 01:05:43,772
-We're about to find out.
-All right!

837
01:05:43,856 --> 01:05:45,649
Let's go kick some booty.

838
01:05:59,163 --> 01:06:00,622
Rachel! No. Rachel!

839
01:06:01,915 --> 01:06:02,999
In a minute.

840
01:06:08,714 --> 01:06:09,673
Stop right there!

841
01:06:10,382 --> 01:06:11,591
Get the bag.

842
01:06:19,808 --> 01:06:21,351
He's gonna come back down, right?

843
01:06:21,435 --> 01:06:22,894
I don't know.

844
01:06:22,978 --> 01:06:23,979
Good luck!

845
01:06:26,148 --> 01:06:28,483
Look. Tom and Sonic have to be inside.

846
01:06:29,193 --> 01:06:30,986
I got a fiancé to vaporize.

847
01:06:31,069 --> 01:06:32,570
-Watch your back, sis.
-Okay.

848
01:06:35,449 --> 01:06:36,450
Randall!

849
01:06:44,082 --> 01:06:46,125
We got her. Move in.

850
01:06:50,547 --> 01:06:51,589
Okay.

851
01:07:07,231 --> 01:07:09,149
I did not mean to do that!

852
01:07:21,912 --> 01:07:23,872
Something bothering you, Agent?

853
01:07:23,956 --> 01:07:26,625
I just feel a little guilty
about what I did to Rachel, sir.

854
01:07:27,751 --> 01:07:30,003
Don't worry about it.
We'll send her a gift card.

855
01:07:30,087 --> 01:07:32,214
Now, I propose a toast.

856
01:07:35,425 --> 01:07:38,219
To a perfectly executed operation.

857
01:07:42,891 --> 01:07:44,559
Sir, we're under attack.

858
01:08:04,955 --> 01:08:08,458
Randall, wifey's home!

859
01:08:13,130 --> 01:08:14,756
Oh, my God. Rachel.

860
01:08:39,448 --> 01:08:42,284
What a woman.

861
01:08:44,453 --> 01:08:45,662
You no-good,

862
01:08:46,913 --> 01:08:49,916
lowdown, dirty, lying--

863
01:08:50,000 --> 01:08:51,209
Rachel, just listen to me.

864
01:08:51,293 --> 01:08:55,547
What kind of twisted sicko
tricks someone into a fake wedding?

865
01:08:57,966 --> 01:09:00,176
Party's over, Bridezilla.
Stop right there.

866
01:09:01,511 --> 01:09:03,638
You son of a--

867
01:09:03,722 --> 01:09:05,265
-Have it your way.
-No!

868
01:09:05,974 --> 01:09:07,600
No!

869
01:09:12,522 --> 01:09:14,857
Very disappointing, Agent Handel.

870
01:09:17,778 --> 01:09:21,198
-Is that supposed to be a weapon?
-I don't know, but we gonna find out.

871
01:09:21,281 --> 01:09:23,700
Haven't you caused enough trouble
for one day?

872
01:09:23,784 --> 01:09:26,077
I haven't even begun causing trouble.

873
01:09:26,745 --> 01:09:29,873
Hell hath no fury like a bride scorned.

874
01:09:36,713 --> 01:09:39,006
Looks like it's real, huh?

875
01:09:43,261 --> 01:09:44,595
No. Right.

876
01:09:46,515 --> 01:09:49,100
Be honest. How bad is it?

877
01:09:49,685 --> 01:09:52,312
Not bad at all.
You got Tased. You'll be fine.

878
01:09:56,900 --> 01:10:00,320
-I'm so cold.
-You landed on our ice sculpture.

879
01:10:00,404 --> 01:10:01,488
Get up.

880
01:10:09,204 --> 01:10:12,081
Just tell me the truth, for once.

881
01:10:13,250 --> 01:10:17,420
Is there anything about you
or about us that was real?

882
01:10:18,213 --> 01:10:21,549
Rachel, look at me.

883
01:10:22,884 --> 01:10:26,512
Before I met you, I didn't think
that I was even capable of real happiness.

884
01:10:28,181 --> 01:10:30,433
But that all changed
when you walked into my life.

885
01:10:31,560 --> 01:10:34,312
And I ended up breaking the first rule
of undercover work.

886
01:10:35,021 --> 01:10:36,397
Which is?

887
01:10:37,149 --> 01:10:38,525
Never fall in love.

888
01:10:51,705 --> 01:10:54,374
-Maddie!
-We're busting out of here.

889
01:10:54,458 --> 01:10:55,667
How'd you get past the guards?

890
01:10:55,751 --> 01:10:57,586
Because that little fox
is into some crazy stuff.

891
01:10:57,669 --> 01:10:58,711
Come on.

892
01:11:00,297 --> 01:11:01,840
-Let's go.
-You're amazing.

893
01:11:12,642 --> 01:11:15,311
The Owls were fools to think
they could hide this.

894
01:11:53,767 --> 01:11:54,934
What's happening?

895
01:11:56,561 --> 01:11:58,229
Wait for it.

896
01:12:09,783 --> 01:12:12,035
Yes. Eureka!

897
01:12:13,245 --> 01:12:14,955
I've found it!

898
01:12:34,432 --> 01:12:35,558
Sonic.

899
01:12:37,519 --> 01:12:39,270
-What is that?
-A big problem.

900
01:12:40,313 --> 01:12:42,231
The compass led Robotnik to the Emerald.

901
01:12:42,315 --> 01:12:44,317
That's got to be hundreds of miles away.

902
01:12:45,777 --> 01:12:49,197
All right. Huddle up.
Let's figure out a plan.

903
01:12:49,281 --> 01:12:51,324
-Together.
-There's no time for that.

904
01:12:51,408 --> 01:12:53,368
I'm the only one
that can get there fast enough.

905
01:12:53,451 --> 01:12:56,328
Sonic, this is way too big for you
to do by yourself.

906
01:12:56,913 --> 01:12:58,414
You see that little fox over there?

907
01:12:58,999 --> 01:13:02,002
He came all the way across the universe
to meet his hero.

908
01:13:02,085 --> 01:13:05,004
And what did his hero do?
I practically got him killed.

909
01:13:05,881 --> 01:13:07,841
You know what? You were right.

910
01:13:08,383 --> 01:13:11,969
My moment came and I blew it. I'm no hero.

911
01:13:12,053 --> 01:13:13,220
-Wait.

912
01:13:13,305 --> 01:13:15,640
I'm not letting anyone else get hurt
because of me.

913
01:13:15,724 --> 01:13:17,600
I'm gonna fix this while I still can.

914
01:13:19,102 --> 01:13:20,728
Sonic!

915
01:13:20,812 --> 01:13:22,230
Sonic, wait!

916
01:13:25,066 --> 01:13:26,942
Hold on. Wait.

917
01:13:27,027 --> 01:13:29,529
-Don't move.
-Take it easy, little guy. You're hurt.

918
01:13:29,613 --> 01:13:33,283
But we have to help him.
You don't know what he's up against.

919
01:13:40,498 --> 01:13:41,874
You believe us now?

920
01:13:49,007 --> 01:13:50,091
Hey, Bob!

921
01:13:50,175 --> 01:13:51,926
Hey, Maria, how you doing?

922
01:13:55,472 --> 01:13:56,514
Working on my moves.

923
01:13:56,598 --> 01:13:59,225
Just keepin' it green.
No need to burn the fuel.

924
01:13:59,309 --> 01:14:00,310
Speaking of fuel--

925
01:14:06,733 --> 01:14:08,109
Closed?

926
01:14:09,694 --> 01:14:10,903
That doesn't seem right.

927
01:14:23,708 --> 01:14:24,750
Close.

928
01:14:29,297 --> 01:14:30,589
Yes.

929
01:14:30,674 --> 01:14:33,218
Makeover, makeover. Look at you.

930
01:14:33,301 --> 01:14:34,635
Freeze! Police!

931
01:14:36,012 --> 01:14:38,097
Oh, my God, you got robot hands.

932
01:14:38,181 --> 01:14:41,559
-No, they're gloves.
-Get 'em up. Now spread your fingers!

933
01:14:42,894 --> 01:14:45,521
Now wiggle 'em! Wiggle your digits!

934
01:14:46,982 --> 01:14:49,651
Yes! Like you just finished
a big musical number.

935
01:14:51,486 --> 01:14:53,029
Good.

936
01:14:53,113 --> 01:14:54,531
Why is there a light on your head?

937
01:14:58,451 --> 01:15:00,494
'Cause I'm the sheriff
for the weekend, pal.

938
01:15:09,629 --> 01:15:10,588
Water.

939
01:15:10,672 --> 01:15:12,548
Why did it have to be water?

940
01:15:15,969 --> 01:15:18,304
Okay, you can do this.

941
01:15:21,641 --> 01:15:23,517
I gotta go fast.

942
01:17:06,121 --> 01:17:09,457
I don't want to die like this!
It's derivative!

943
01:17:11,000 --> 01:17:12,668
Make room for Daddy!

944
01:17:20,635 --> 01:17:21,802
Two and two.

945
01:17:21,886 --> 01:17:25,139
Great! We're still bipedals, more or less.

946
01:17:28,434 --> 01:17:29,977
Fire in the hole!

947
01:17:32,188 --> 01:17:35,399
I've solved it. There is a booby trap
every seven seco--

948
01:17:42,073 --> 01:17:43,449
That was a little early.

949
01:17:44,951 --> 01:17:48,537
So glad it didn't cut off my mustache.

950
01:17:48,621 --> 01:17:51,040
Hey, Little Red Wrecking Ball.

951
01:17:51,875 --> 01:17:54,210
I know you're dying
to get your Emerald on,

952
01:17:54,294 --> 01:17:58,006
but can we be a little bit more mindful
of our surroundings?

953
01:17:58,506 --> 01:17:59,548
May 1?

954
01:18:06,181 --> 01:18:08,766
In 30 feet turn left.

955
01:18:08,850 --> 01:18:10,726
Work smarter, not harder.

956
01:18:32,165 --> 01:18:33,541
My pelvis.

957
01:18:37,921 --> 01:18:42,050
Okay, Secret Temple,
let's see what you've got.

958
01:18:50,350 --> 01:18:51,851
No, no, no! No!

959
01:18:56,564 --> 01:18:57,565
No.

960
01:18:58,733 --> 01:18:59,734
Yes!

961
01:19:05,698 --> 01:19:07,616
You have arrived at your destination.

962
01:19:07,700 --> 01:19:10,703
Wow. That really opened up the space.

963
01:19:10,787 --> 01:19:13,748
I can't even picture it
with an impenetrable wall now.

964
01:19:13,831 --> 01:19:15,749
And the rubble is always a nice touch.

965
01:19:24,968 --> 01:19:28,680
At last. The Master Emerald.

966
01:19:28,763 --> 01:19:30,014
Ultimate power.

967
01:19:30,098 --> 01:19:32,934
Soon order will be restored.

968
01:19:33,017 --> 01:19:36,353
All because of what we have done together.

969
01:19:36,437 --> 01:19:38,730
Such a lovely sentiment, Knuckles.

970
01:19:39,232 --> 01:19:41,817
I think I feel a single tear forming.

971
01:19:44,779 --> 01:19:46,030
Sadly...

972
01:19:47,198 --> 01:19:51,698
you're as useful to me now
as a backstage pass to Limp Bizkit.

973
01:20:06,426 --> 01:20:07,593
Nailed it.

974
01:20:08,678 --> 01:20:12,223
This guy is always trying to spoil
a bad thing!

975
01:20:13,558 --> 01:20:16,060
You guys are here, too?
Took the long way, huh?

976
01:20:16,144 --> 01:20:18,312
Is everything a joke to you?

977
01:20:18,396 --> 01:20:21,357
Why must you constantly interfere
with my destiny?

978
01:20:21,441 --> 01:20:25,111
Because my destiny is to protect
my friends and family.

979
01:20:25,194 --> 01:20:27,362
I think I just threw up in my mouth.

980
01:20:28,156 --> 01:20:32,656
And if you want that emerald,
you're gonna have to go through me.

981
01:20:55,641 --> 01:20:58,685
The Echidna's taking no prisoners today!

982
01:20:58,770 --> 01:21:02,523
Sonic has heart,
but will he lose the quill to live?

983
01:21:04,359 --> 01:21:08,029
I don't want to fight you,
but you're not giving me much choice.

984
01:21:14,744 --> 01:21:17,496
Too easy. Let's do this.

985
01:21:44,649 --> 01:21:49,070
Why don't you stand still
and die with honor?

986
01:21:49,153 --> 01:21:50,404
Let me think about it.

987
01:21:50,488 --> 01:21:54,158
Okay, I thought about it and I pass.

988
01:22:03,626 --> 01:22:05,085
Hi there, beautiful.

989
01:22:06,379 --> 01:22:08,381
You're the real deal, aren't you?

990
01:22:09,090 --> 01:22:12,510
Where have you been all my life?

991
01:22:16,347 --> 01:22:18,766
Say goodbye, hedgehog.

992
01:22:22,270 --> 01:22:25,189
Knuckles, stop.
Robotnik's stealing the Emerald!

993
01:22:25,273 --> 01:22:27,733
What kind of fool do you take me for?

994
01:22:27,817 --> 01:22:29,068
Just look.

995
01:22:31,612 --> 01:22:32,946
Mine.

996
01:22:34,198 --> 01:22:36,909
Wait! That wasn't the deal.

997
01:22:40,371 --> 01:22:42,998
You poor, naive creature.

998
01:22:43,082 --> 01:22:44,500
It's not your fault.

999
01:22:44,584 --> 01:22:48,212
A more advanced intellect would have seen
this move coming a mile away.

1000
01:22:48,296 --> 01:22:50,131
Or 1.6 kilometers.

1001
01:22:50,631 --> 01:22:53,383
But I trusted you! You were my friend!

1002
01:23:00,516 --> 01:23:02,935
I'm sorry. That just hit me funny.

1003
01:23:03,853 --> 01:23:08,353
Let this be my final lesson to you,
you dim-witted celestial skin tag.

1004
01:23:09,859 --> 01:23:11,235
Friends...

1005
01:23:11,319 --> 01:23:15,323
are open, honest
and vulnerable with each other.

1006
01:23:15,406 --> 01:23:17,950
Which means X squared
times the hypotenuse of Y squared,

1007
01:23:18,034 --> 01:23:20,870
divided by the absolute value
of friendship, equals...

1008
01:23:21,370 --> 01:23:22,412
dookie!

1009
01:23:22,497 --> 01:23:23,748
Oh, no.

1010
01:23:31,881 --> 01:23:36,381
Chaos is power!

1011
01:23:55,196 --> 01:23:56,947
Let's get out of here!

1012
01:24:09,502 --> 01:24:10,669
Knuckles!

1013
01:24:15,132 --> 01:24:18,009
Water again? Come on!

1014
01:25:16,736 --> 01:25:20,740
-You saved me.
-Don't talk to me. I'm not in the mood.

1015
01:25:22,158 --> 01:25:26,162
How dare you attack me
in my hour of sorrow!

1016
01:25:27,038 --> 01:25:28,497
Why did you save me?

1017
01:25:30,541 --> 01:25:32,376
Because you saved me first,

1018
01:25:32,460 --> 01:25:36,130
which clearly gave you
a tactical advantage I do not understand.

1019
01:25:36,213 --> 01:25:39,841
It wasn't a tactic.
I couldn't just let you die.

1020
01:25:40,885 --> 01:25:45,385
Why? I've been trying to destroy you
since the moment we met.

1021
01:25:45,681 --> 01:25:49,601
Because being a hero
isn't about taking care of yourself.

1022
01:25:49,685 --> 01:25:53,105
It's about taking responsibility
for other people.

1023
01:25:55,399 --> 01:25:58,652
Wise words. An ancient Earth proverb?

1024
01:25:58,736 --> 01:26:01,155
No, sir,
that's a Wachowski family special.

1025
01:26:01,238 --> 01:26:03,240
I got it from a guy in a rowboat.

1026
01:26:03,991 --> 01:26:05,492
Someone who means a lot to me.

1027
01:26:07,411 --> 01:26:08,995
Wait a second. What's that sound?

1028
01:26:11,165 --> 01:26:14,668
Only Sonic the Hedgehog
needs rescuing this much.

1029
01:26:15,836 --> 01:26:17,712
That sly little fox!

1030
01:26:20,257 --> 01:26:22,592
Come on, Knucklehead. We're not beat yet.

1031
01:26:23,427 --> 01:26:25,929
On the mountain,
you told me you'd lost everything.

1032
01:26:26,555 --> 01:26:28,056
The way I did.

1033
01:26:28,140 --> 01:26:30,892
But you seem so hopeful and free.

1034
01:26:31,894 --> 01:26:35,480
How did you move forward
despite failing again?

1035
01:26:36,232 --> 01:26:39,360
And again. And again.
And again. And again.

1036
01:26:39,443 --> 01:26:43,071
Okay, I didn't fail that much.
But I didn't do this all alone.

1037
01:26:43,155 --> 01:26:45,740
I found a new family. New friends.

1038
01:26:45,825 --> 01:26:47,243
And you can too.

1039
01:26:49,537 --> 01:26:51,956
You don't have to be alone anymore.

1040
01:26:57,044 --> 01:26:59,212
Are you kidding me with that handshake?

1041
01:27:01,841 --> 01:27:03,259
I'm done playing games, pal.

1042
01:27:04,927 --> 01:27:06,678
You're gonna tell me what I want to know.

1043
01:27:09,098 --> 01:27:12,476
And I am asking you for the last time...

1044
01:27:14,812 --> 01:27:17,272
what would you like on your bagel?

1045
01:27:17,356 --> 01:27:19,274
I'm not telling you anything.

1046
01:27:19,358 --> 01:27:22,277
And that is a display bagel.

1047
01:27:22,361 --> 01:27:25,572
I don't get it with you!
I mean, I've tried everything.

1048
01:27:25,656 --> 01:27:29,284
I was good cop. I was bad cop.
I was cop who offers you a bagel.

1049
01:27:29,368 --> 01:27:30,369
And nothing. It's like--

1050
01:27:30,453 --> 01:27:32,705
That is a display bagel. Wow.

1051
01:27:41,964 --> 01:27:43,715
Doctor, you're here.

1052
01:27:45,718 --> 01:27:50,218
Yes, I'm here, and yet I'm...

1053
01:27:51,932 --> 01:27:53,600
not all there.

1054
01:27:53,684 --> 01:27:55,185
Sir, are you feeling okay?

1055
01:27:55,269 --> 01:27:59,398
I'm more than okay.

1056
01:28:00,024 --> 01:28:03,152
I'm upgraded.

1057
01:28:03,235 --> 01:28:06,279
Sinister 3.0.

1058
01:28:06,363 --> 01:28:10,367
My game is next level.

1059
01:28:15,456 --> 01:28:16,623
Hi.

1060
01:28:19,460 --> 01:28:23,960
I can smell the electricity in your brain.

1061
01:28:27,468 --> 01:28:29,761
You smell like a snack plate.

1062
01:28:31,180 --> 01:28:34,308
Yeah, that's fair. I had a couple today.

1063
01:28:34,850 --> 01:28:36,309
Sit down.

1064
01:28:40,981 --> 01:28:42,399
In the chair.

1065
01:28:45,611 --> 01:28:46,778
I didn't know.

1066
01:28:47,863 --> 01:28:50,949
"Cause he was in the chair,
so I didn't-- Okay.

1067
01:28:51,033 --> 01:28:52,951
Sir? We have a problem.

1068
01:28:58,791 --> 01:29:01,418
-All teams in position!
-Set up a perimeter!

1069
01:29:01,919 --> 01:29:03,462
Move! Move! Move!

1070
01:29:18,602 --> 01:29:22,230
In correct us, my trusty barnacle.

1071
01:29:23,566 --> 01:29:26,026
After all these years,

1072
01:29:26,694 --> 01:29:28,404
what I finally got...

1073
01:29:29,572 --> 01:29:31,615
is a solution.

1074
01:29:42,251 --> 01:29:44,127
-Commander.
-Status report.

1075
01:29:44,211 --> 01:29:47,589
Robotnik is in there with Stone
and a hostage. Possibly local PD.

1076
01:29:47,673 --> 01:29:51,051
I'm not saying he's dumb,
but if he is local PD,

1077
01:29:51,135 --> 01:29:52,761
this town's in a lot of trouble.

1078
01:29:53,512 --> 01:29:54,804
Wade.

1079
01:30:09,194 --> 01:30:10,195
Okay.

1080
01:30:11,155 --> 01:30:13,699
Rockin' that new spring collection, I see.

1081
01:30:13,782 --> 01:30:18,282
Well, if it isn't the Pastry King.

1082
01:30:18,412 --> 01:30:19,538
The Donut Lord.

1083
01:30:20,039 --> 01:30:21,832
A real genius would remember
the name of the guy

1084
01:30:21,916 --> 01:30:23,834
who helped kick your butt off this planet.

1085
01:30:23,918 --> 01:30:25,878
And I'll do it again if you mess
with Green Hills.

1086
01:30:26,962 --> 01:30:30,757
Congratulations on your oh-so-temporary
sense of superiority.

1087
01:30:30,841 --> 01:30:33,176
You're finished, Robotnik!
We've taken everything.

1088
01:30:33,260 --> 01:30:35,971
Your lab, your drones, your funding!

1089
01:30:36,055 --> 01:30:39,224
Let's see how big of a man you are
without your silly little robots.

1090
01:30:40,976 --> 01:30:42,894
Would you like to see...

1091
01:30:44,355 --> 01:30:46,482
how big a man I can be?

1092
01:30:57,368 --> 01:31:00,537
Welcome to the new norm.

1093
01:31:10,839 --> 01:31:12,215
My God!

1094
01:31:15,719 --> 01:31:19,431
Doctor! Take me with you!

1095
01:31:43,872 --> 01:31:45,707
He's taking everything apart.

1096
01:31:46,709 --> 01:31:48,127
He's building something.

1097
01:31:56,135 --> 01:31:58,512
That can only be one thing.

1098
01:31:58,595 --> 01:32:00,972
The fearsome power of the Emerald.

1099
01:32:01,056 --> 01:32:05,060
If that thing really turns thoughts
into power, we are in big trouble.

1100
01:32:05,144 --> 01:32:07,187
Robotnik has a lot of bad thoughts.

1101
01:32:07,271 --> 01:32:10,232
Hey, Sonic,
are you sure it was a good idea

1102
01:32:10,315 --> 01:32:11,816
bringing you-know-who aboard?

1103
01:32:11,900 --> 01:32:15,653
Knuckles isn't really a bad guy.
He's just a little mixed up.

1104
01:32:15,738 --> 01:32:17,448
I am not mixed up!

1105
01:32:17,531 --> 01:32:22,031
I have steely focus. And I'm complex.
And that's a lot for some people.

1106
01:32:23,245 --> 01:32:25,872
Hope you're not still mad
I hit you with that car.

1107
01:32:26,623 --> 01:32:28,374
I was completely uninjured.

1108
01:32:28,459 --> 01:32:31,628
And my revenge will come
when you least expect it, fox.

1109
01:33:03,077 --> 01:33:05,662
Sir, you're magnificent!

1110
01:33:05,746 --> 01:33:07,789
Thank you, sycophant.

1111
01:33:07,873 --> 01:33:10,292
Your admiration is inevitable.

1112
01:33:20,344 --> 01:33:21,803
I knew it!

1113
01:33:21,887 --> 01:33:24,389
Just like the Stay Puft Marshmallow Man.

1114
01:33:25,474 --> 01:33:27,517
World Domination play list.

1115
01:33:40,864 --> 01:33:42,031
Fall back.

1116
01:33:43,450 --> 01:33:46,286
Fall back! Quick! Retreat!

1117
01:33:48,288 --> 01:33:50,373
How are we supposed to beat this thing?

1118
01:33:50,457 --> 01:33:51,499
We need a plan.

1119
01:33:51,583 --> 01:33:53,626
Knuckles, use your strength to--

1120
01:33:54,211 --> 01:33:56,546
Jump off the plane. Wow.

1121
01:33:56,630 --> 01:34:00,550
Okay, this is what we're gonna do.
Step 1: Light taunting.

1122
01:34:00,634 --> 01:34:02,385
Step 2: I have no idea.

1123
01:34:05,514 --> 01:34:06,681
Sonic!

1124
01:34:09,852 --> 01:34:11,812
Nice action figure, Eggman.

1125
01:34:11,895 --> 01:34:14,814
Does it do anything
or just stand there looking ugly?

1126
01:34:18,485 --> 01:34:21,154
Like a blister, he keeps coming back!

1127
01:34:22,156 --> 01:34:25,117
He's on the okay-to-kill list.
Shoot the missiles. Make a decision.

1128
01:34:25,200 --> 01:34:27,994
I need a moment, sir.
I'm trying to figure out how to do this.

1129
01:34:28,078 --> 01:34:30,163
Did you even glance at a manual?

1130
01:34:30,247 --> 01:34:32,415
-No!
-I'll do it.

1131
01:34:32,499 --> 01:34:33,917
Pardon my lightning.

1132
01:34:34,001 --> 01:34:35,877
You might want to ground yourself.

1133
01:34:38,046 --> 01:34:39,047
Uh-oh.

1134
01:34:39,131 --> 01:34:41,675
I'm gonna pop that thing open
like a can of chili--

1135
01:34:44,219 --> 01:34:45,678
Hang on!

1136
01:34:58,984 --> 01:35:01,236
-Yeah!
-Close one.

1137
01:35:02,029 --> 01:35:03,113
Sonic!

1138
01:35:06,867 --> 01:35:08,451
Robotnik!

1139
01:35:10,078 --> 01:35:11,537
Deceiver!

1140
01:35:11,622 --> 01:35:13,415
Die, mosquito.

1141
01:35:25,844 --> 01:35:26,845
I felt that.

1142
01:35:46,031 --> 01:35:47,490
What just happened?

1143
01:35:47,574 --> 01:35:50,827
It's the Stache Masher.
Right here in the manual.

1144
01:35:53,121 --> 01:35:55,456
Return to sender.

1145
01:36:03,048 --> 01:36:04,382
Stone?

1146
01:36:05,884 --> 01:36:10,054
Great. Next thing you know, there'll be
a report about a hostile work environment.

1147
01:36:13,141 --> 01:36:16,310
Those were our best attacks,
and they did nothing!

1148
01:36:16,395 --> 01:36:20,232
We can't beat Robotnik as long as he's got
that Emerald. He's too powerful.

1149
01:36:20,315 --> 01:36:23,401
Look, we aren't strong enough
to beat Robotnik on our own.

1150
01:36:23,485 --> 01:36:24,736
But there's three of us.

1151
01:36:24,820 --> 01:36:27,989
Your strength, your smarts and my speed.

1152
01:36:28,073 --> 01:36:29,741
Together. That's how we win.

1153
01:36:29,825 --> 01:36:34,287
So we make our stand here
on the field of battle.

1154
01:36:34,371 --> 01:36:35,747
As a team.

1155
01:36:35,831 --> 01:36:37,332
This is it.

1156
01:36:38,709 --> 01:36:41,378
This is our moment.

1157
01:36:43,422 --> 01:36:44,923
Time to fight.

1158
01:36:52,431 --> 01:36:55,851
Bad time to say this,
but I don't actually have a plan.

1159
01:36:56,852 --> 01:36:58,687
Tails, any ideas?

1160
01:36:58,770 --> 01:37:00,438
We have to find his weak spot.

1161
01:37:00,522 --> 01:37:02,148
I suggest the groin.

1162
01:37:02,232 --> 01:37:04,317
What? No. No!

1163
01:37:04,401 --> 01:37:06,986
Traditionally, yes,
the groin is the weakest spot.

1164
01:37:07,070 --> 01:37:09,113
Stop saying "groin."

1165
01:37:09,197 --> 01:37:10,990
Hedgehog!

1166
01:37:11,074 --> 01:37:12,408
Look out!

1167
01:37:15,203 --> 01:37:17,705
I know what his weak spot is. It's me.

1168
01:37:17,789 --> 01:37:19,540
I'm the groin!

1169
01:37:22,169 --> 01:37:25,130
Think about it.
I live rent-free in this dude's head.

1170
01:37:25,213 --> 01:37:27,048
So if I go out there and rile him up...

1171
01:37:27,132 --> 01:37:29,551
He'll focus on only you,
leaving himself open

1172
01:37:29,634 --> 01:37:31,886
to a flanking maneuver
from me and the fox!

1173
01:37:31,970 --> 01:37:34,722
Hedgehog,
you are a brave and noble warrior.

1174
01:37:34,806 --> 01:37:37,475
Go to your certain death with honor.

1175
01:37:37,559 --> 01:37:40,103
We're gonna have to work
on your pep talks, pal.

1176
01:37:40,187 --> 01:37:41,980
-Yeah.
-Let's go.

1177
01:37:45,692 --> 01:37:47,318
All right, mustache.

1178
01:37:47,402 --> 01:37:50,238
You want me? Come and get me.

1179
01:37:50,322 --> 01:37:53,074
You don't tell me
about coming and getting.

1180
01:37:53,158 --> 01:37:55,535
I am on the cutting edge
of coming and getting!

1181
01:37:55,619 --> 01:37:57,537
Coming, getting.

1182
01:37:57,621 --> 01:38:01,791
Coming, getting.
Coming, getting. Coming, getting.

1183
01:38:04,378 --> 01:38:06,463
You're really heavy.

1184
01:38:06,546 --> 01:38:10,383
That's because I am
one million percent muscle. Faster, fox!

1185
01:38:12,594 --> 01:38:15,763
-Go! Move, guys! Move back!
-Let's go, that's it! Go, go, go!

1186
01:38:15,847 --> 01:38:16,889
-Keep going!
-Go! Go!

1187
01:38:16,973 --> 01:38:18,849
-No, no! Stop!
-Stop the truck!

1188
01:38:18,934 --> 01:38:20,226
Tom, what happened here?

1189
01:38:21,269 --> 01:38:23,187
-You thinking what I'm thinking?
-Let's get our kid.

1190
01:38:23,271 --> 01:38:24,647
We need your truck!

1191
01:38:30,862 --> 01:38:33,072
Coming, getting.

1192
01:38:34,074 --> 01:38:36,076
Yoo-hoo!

1193
01:38:36,159 --> 01:38:38,077
So what's the plan here?

1194
01:38:38,662 --> 01:38:43,041
You gonna build a big robot house?
Get yourself a big robot wife?

1195
01:38:43,125 --> 01:38:47,462
I'm going to enslave humanity
and force them to service my machines.

1196
01:38:47,546 --> 01:38:50,382
First, Green Hills. Then the universe.

1197
01:38:50,465 --> 01:38:51,716
Then the multiverse.

1198
01:38:51,800 --> 01:38:54,511
Then who knows? Maybe that'll be enough.

1199
01:38:55,178 --> 01:38:56,470
Full disclosure?

1200
01:38:57,347 --> 01:38:59,932
You won't be there.

1201
01:39:04,479 --> 01:39:06,606
Eye lasers? Really?

1202
01:39:19,077 --> 01:39:21,037
Snot rocket!

1203
01:39:22,622 --> 01:39:23,664
No, no, no!

1204
01:39:32,174 --> 01:39:33,675
Giving up already?

1205
01:39:33,758 --> 01:39:37,470
Not so tough when you're fighting someone
700 times your size, are ya?

1206
01:39:39,598 --> 01:39:42,058
You can't beat me!

1207
01:39:42,142 --> 01:39:45,353
I'm all-powerful! All-knowing!

1208
01:39:48,064 --> 01:39:50,274
All-seeing.

1209
01:39:51,401 --> 01:39:53,736
Looks like your fancy robot has a glitch.

1210
01:39:53,820 --> 01:39:57,073
Is it me? What about me? I'm over here.
Up top! Down below! Behind you!

1211
01:39:58,074 --> 01:39:59,992
I'm over here. Sorry! Over here.

1212
01:40:00,619 --> 01:40:01,828
Too slow! Try again.

1213
01:40:01,912 --> 01:40:03,955
-You can't outsmart me.
-Missed me again.

1214
01:40:04,039 --> 01:40:05,832
I'm the out smarter-er!

1215
01:40:10,170 --> 01:40:13,131
I didn't outsmart you.
I'm just the distraction.

1216
01:40:13,215 --> 01:40:14,507
Robotnik!

1217
01:40:15,133 --> 01:40:17,885
I am also a hologram.

1218
01:40:17,969 --> 01:40:19,887
Disloyal.

1219
01:40:19,971 --> 01:40:22,807
"Dis" is how I roll.

1220
01:40:51,211 --> 01:40:52,754
Where's my Emerald?

1221
01:40:53,505 --> 01:40:55,381
No, no, no, no!

1222
01:40:55,465 --> 01:40:57,800
Computer, auxiliary power.

1223
01:41:07,143 --> 01:41:09,395
The Emerald. It's right there.

1224
01:41:09,938 --> 01:41:11,856
Move, you hunk of junk!

1225
01:41:16,403 --> 01:41:19,781
I have to... reach it.

1226
01:41:43,013 --> 01:41:44,014
Come on.

1227
01:41:46,182 --> 01:41:48,350
There he is! Go! Go, go, go!

1228
01:41:57,277 --> 01:41:58,319
No!

1229
01:41:58,403 --> 01:41:59,695
We got you, Sonic.

1230
01:42:00,905 --> 01:42:02,323
Hold on!

1231
01:42:15,545 --> 01:42:17,797
-You guys okay?
-Yeah.

1232
01:42:19,299 --> 01:42:20,341
Okay.

1233
01:42:25,889 --> 01:42:27,932
I got the Emerald.
We could still defeat him.

1234
01:42:28,016 --> 01:42:31,185
Come on, come on.
How does this thing work? What do I do?

1235
01:42:32,395 --> 01:42:33,562
What?

1236
01:42:34,230 --> 01:42:36,941
No. No, no, no!

1237
01:42:40,820 --> 01:42:44,990
Look at the happy little family.

1238
01:42:50,872 --> 01:42:53,374
You have to get away from me.
I'm the one he wants.

1239
01:42:53,458 --> 01:42:54,459
Hey.

1240
01:42:54,959 --> 01:42:56,585
We're not going anywhere.

1241
01:42:57,170 --> 01:42:58,337
We're family.

1242
01:43:01,925 --> 01:43:03,593
And families stick together...

1243
01:43:06,471 --> 01:43:07,680
no matter what.

1244
01:43:10,809 --> 01:43:11,935
I love you guys.

1245
01:43:12,852 --> 01:43:14,395
We love you too, Sonic.

1246
01:43:22,904 --> 01:43:24,363
No!

1247
01:43:26,408 --> 01:43:28,576
I got him!

1248
01:43:28,660 --> 01:43:32,246
I finally got him!

1249
01:43:37,711 --> 01:43:39,462
What was that?

1250
01:44:25,341 --> 01:44:27,551
It's over, Eggman.

1251
01:44:28,928 --> 01:44:31,639
I like the new look. It works for you.

1252
01:44:32,223 --> 01:44:35,226
What do you say
we just let bygones be bygones?

1253
01:44:35,310 --> 01:44:39,063
I did some things, you did some things.
There are good people on both sides.

1254
01:44:40,774 --> 01:44:43,860
Surely two intelligent beings

1255
01:44:45,612 --> 01:44:47,614
can work these things out!

1256
01:44:59,626 --> 01:45:02,086
-Come on, buddy. Come on.
-Get him, Sonic!

1257
01:45:02,170 --> 01:45:03,504
Yeah. Come on.

1258
01:45:20,063 --> 01:45:21,522
It's like that?

1259
01:45:23,024 --> 01:45:25,317
Okay, we're not friends.

1260
01:45:29,739 --> 01:45:32,032
Later, hater!

1261
01:45:43,419 --> 01:45:44,878
-Sonic!
-Buddy!

1262
01:45:45,463 --> 01:45:47,506
Wait! You cannot touch him!

1263
01:45:47,590 --> 01:45:50,259
The hedgehog holds
the power of the Emerald.

1264
01:45:50,969 --> 01:45:54,555
I am sorry.
He is no longer the Sonic you once knew.

1265
01:45:55,139 --> 01:45:56,140
What?

1266
01:46:16,077 --> 01:46:17,703
You got to try this.

1267
01:46:23,459 --> 01:46:26,795
Okay.
He is exactly the Sonic you once knew.

1268
01:46:28,673 --> 01:46:30,049
-Uh-huh.
-Uh-huh.

1269
01:46:38,516 --> 01:46:39,600
Sonic!

1270
01:46:41,895 --> 01:46:43,479
Bring it in, bud.

1271
01:46:44,939 --> 01:46:46,899
It's good to be back in blue.

1272
01:46:46,983 --> 01:46:50,319
The golden god thing was fun,
but blue has always been more my color.

1273
01:46:50,403 --> 01:46:51,487
Looks good on you.

1274
01:46:51,571 --> 01:46:56,071
Sonic, you were the most powerful hero
in the universe, and you let it go.

1275
01:46:57,076 --> 01:46:58,160
Why?

1276
01:46:59,913 --> 01:47:03,041
Because I still have
some growing up to do.

1277
01:47:05,293 --> 01:47:09,046
-And I kind of like being a kid.
-And you're not just any kid.

1278
01:47:09,631 --> 01:47:11,507
You're our kid.

1279
01:47:11,591 --> 01:47:13,009
That's right.

1280
01:47:13,092 --> 01:47:15,803
-Bring it in!
-Yay. Hugs.

1281
01:47:15,887 --> 01:47:18,723
It's a good thing we didn't do this
before. You would've blown up.

1282
01:47:26,356 --> 01:47:27,940
You fixed it.

1283
01:47:28,024 --> 01:47:31,360
I've spent my whole life
questing for this.

1284
01:47:31,444 --> 01:47:32,736
Now I have it.

1285
01:47:32,820 --> 01:47:34,613
Now we have it.

1286
01:47:34,697 --> 01:47:37,282
What do we do with it? What next?

1287
01:47:37,367 --> 01:47:39,494
There were once two orders of heroes

1288
01:47:39,577 --> 01:47:43,706
who protected the galaxy from those
who would use the Emerald for evil.

1289
01:47:43,790 --> 01:47:47,668
But they have all passed on
to the great battleground in the sky.

1290
01:47:47,752 --> 01:47:51,213
So we start a new order. The three of us.

1291
01:47:51,297 --> 01:47:53,007
This is no light task.

1292
01:47:53,091 --> 01:47:57,591
We must make a vow to use our powers
to keep the universe safe,

1293
01:47:58,554 --> 01:48:00,389
to watch out for each other.

1294
01:48:00,473 --> 01:48:02,183
Our new tribe.

1295
01:48:02,266 --> 01:48:03,392
I know!

1296
01:48:03,476 --> 01:48:05,895
-A power bump!
-Good idea.

1297
01:48:06,938 --> 01:48:10,149
It's an Earth custom.
An unbreakable promise.

1298
01:48:10,733 --> 01:48:12,025
Very well.

1299
01:48:12,819 --> 01:48:15,238
A power bump it is.

1300
01:48:16,406 --> 01:48:18,074
Power bump!

1301
01:48:21,995 --> 01:48:26,124
It's truly a beautiful day for baseball
here in Green Hills.

1302
01:48:26,207 --> 01:48:27,917
An exciting lineup today

1303
01:48:28,001 --> 01:48:31,295
with the debut appearance
of two new players!

1304
01:48:31,379 --> 01:48:35,549
On the mound,
rookie sensation from across the galaxy,

1305
01:48:35,633 --> 01:48:38,177
Miles "Tails" Prower,

1306
01:48:38,261 --> 01:48:42,761
facing off against the powerhouse,
Knuckles the Echidna.

1307
01:48:44,434 --> 01:48:46,310
I don't understand.

1308
01:48:46,394 --> 01:48:48,562
Why am I angry at the enemy ball?

1309
01:48:48,646 --> 01:48:49,813
You're not angry.

1310
01:48:49,897 --> 01:48:53,150
You just want to hit it as hard as you can
and then run around the bases.

1311
01:48:53,234 --> 01:48:57,734
But if my quest ends where I am standing,
why run at all?

1312
01:48:58,531 --> 01:49:01,075
I can't with this guy. Why do I even try?

1313
01:49:01,159 --> 01:49:03,828
This is just a game.
We're out here having fun.

1314
01:49:03,911 --> 01:49:05,412
Just having some fun.

1315
01:49:05,496 --> 01:49:06,914
Fun.

1316
01:49:08,124 --> 01:49:10,501
All right! Give him the heat, Tails!

1317
01:49:10,585 --> 01:49:12,503
Hope you're ready for my fastball.

1318
01:49:12,587 --> 01:49:15,047
Your fastball will be dishonored.

1319
01:49:15,131 --> 01:49:17,383
And so will you, fox.

1320
01:49:17,467 --> 01:49:19,844
-Easy, guys!
-Don't think about it too much.

1321
01:49:19,927 --> 01:49:23,347
Just keep your elbow up,
eye on the ball and give it a ride.

1322
01:49:23,431 --> 01:49:24,849
A ride? To where?

1323
01:49:29,103 --> 01:49:30,395
Power bump!

1324
01:49:35,693 --> 01:49:37,152
Victory is mine!

1325
01:49:37,236 --> 01:49:39,780
Hey, no fair! That shouldn't count.

1326
01:49:39,864 --> 01:49:42,116
First base is also mine!

1327
01:49:42,200 --> 01:49:46,700
-I think that was our only ball.
-I have conquered the second of the bases!

1328
01:49:46,871 --> 01:49:48,414
Who wants ice cream?

1329
01:49:48,498 --> 01:49:49,707
Knocked the cover off that.

1330
01:49:49,791 --> 01:49:51,709
-Ice cream!
-Ice cream, yeah!

1331
01:49:52,960 --> 01:49:56,421
I am having the fun! What is ice cream?

1332
01:49:56,506 --> 01:49:59,842
It's a dessert.
If you like fun, you're gonna love it.

1333
01:49:59,926 --> 01:50:03,095
Yum. Dessert. Does it have grapes in it?

1334
01:50:03,179 --> 01:50:04,763
No, not usually.

1335
01:50:04,847 --> 01:50:06,515
I'm proud of our little guy.

1336
01:50:07,391 --> 01:50:10,435
I really like his new friends,
especially the red one.

1337
01:50:10,937 --> 01:50:13,564
-He cracks me up.
-Heck of a swing too.

1338
01:50:13,648 --> 01:50:16,400
Come on, fox.
Our dessert adventure awaits.

1339
01:50:16,484 --> 01:50:17,818
-Good job, guys.
-Yeah.

1340
01:50:17,902 --> 01:50:21,196
You too, baby. Let's go get
some ice cream. Come on, come on.

1341
01:50:22,365 --> 01:50:24,533
I'm happy for you, pal.

1342
01:50:24,617 --> 01:50:27,786
Got your wing men.
Perfect friends to grow up with.

1343
01:50:27,870 --> 01:50:31,164
-Come on, Knuckles.
-My victory chariot!

1344
01:50:33,209 --> 01:50:36,170
I've got a lot more than that... Dad.

1345
01:50:41,634 --> 01:50:42,968
Race you to the truck.

1346
01:50:44,637 --> 01:50:46,055
One, two, three, go!

1347
01:50:46,639 --> 01:50:48,766
No, don't go easy on me. I want your best.

1348
01:50:48,850 --> 01:50:51,811
Sonic, I have just been told
they have sprinkles.

1349
01:50:51,894 --> 01:50:55,564
Ice cream and sprinkles?
This is your new destiny.

1350
01:50:55,648 --> 01:51:00,148
What a perfect meal to celebrate
my victory over you in base of ball.

1351
01:51:00,653 --> 01:51:03,280
-What?
-I mean, you barely beat me.

1352
01:51:03,948 --> 01:51:06,450
You've never been beaten so hard.

1353
01:51:10,872 --> 01:51:12,039
Can't forget this.

1354
01:53:11,409 --> 01:53:13,285
Agent, I want an update.

1355
01:53:13,369 --> 01:53:16,288
Still searching, sir.
We haven't found any sign of Robotnik.

1356
01:53:16,372 --> 01:53:18,707
No one could've survived that crash.

1357
01:53:18,791 --> 01:53:21,376
He's toast. Good riddance.

1358
01:53:21,961 --> 01:53:24,713
What a mess that lunatic made.

1359
01:53:25,298 --> 01:53:28,175
Sir, there's something else.

1360
01:53:28,718 --> 01:53:32,221
When we were wiping Robotnik
off our database, we found something.

1361
01:53:32,305 --> 01:53:36,058
A file buried deep in our system
and dating back over 50 years.

1362
01:53:36,142 --> 01:53:39,061
-What was it?
-Coordinates, sir.

1363
01:53:39,145 --> 01:53:41,021
Coordinates? To what?

1364
01:53:41,772 --> 01:53:43,732
A secret research facility.

1365
01:53:44,358 --> 01:53:45,942
It was a black site, sir.

1366
01:53:46,694 --> 01:53:49,154
Someone worked very hard
to keep this hidden.

1367
01:53:50,531 --> 01:53:51,740
My God.

1368
01:53:52,700 --> 01:53:54,034
Project Shadow.

